NomadLoop is a digital audio host focused on live-looping, real-time metacomposition and analysis, exceptional support for non-keyboard MIDI controllers, and multitouch control.

It is based on Julian Storen's excellent JUCE library for C++, and released under the terms of the GNU GPL.


== Building ==

=== Ubuntu ===
1) get premake from http://sourceforge.net/projects/premake/files/Premake/3.7/premake-linux-3.7.tar.gz/download (On 64-bit Linux, you'll need to compile it from source)

2) apt-get install g++ libfreetype6-dev libx11-dev libxinerama-dev libxcursor-dev libxss-dev libjack-dev 

3) cd nomadloop/extras/nomadloop/build/linux/

4) ./runpremake

5) make

6) ./build/NomadLoop

